Snow accumulation in Lone Tree often differs from conditions at Denver International Airport by 2-4 inches, which doesn't sound significant until you realize that most transportation companies have weather cancellation policies that trigger at specific accumulation levels. A storm that drops 4 inches at DIA and 7 inches in Lone Tree means your flight operates on schedule but your ground transportation gets cancelled.

The opposite situation creates different problems. I've experienced situations where Lone Tree has clear roads but the transportation company cancels service due to weather conditions along their primary routes. E-470 maintenance and snow removal operates independently from CDOT highway maintenance, which means the toll road sometimes remains clear when I-25 and C-470 have weather-related problems.

